For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Maintain FTW/School or combination of the two, and if not so fully engaged, complete 10 hours CS per week.

Maintain absolute sobriety from and no possession of alcohol.  

No bars, taverns, liquors stores and beer tents.  

No contact with victim, B.L.L. unless approved by agent.  

No contact with females under the age of 18, or as approved by agent, excluding incidentals while at work.  

No use of any social media including SnapChat.

If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.  

A copy of the police report has been electronically sent to the probation office.

Sex Offender assessment, treatment, counseling.  

Any other Assessments/Treatment/Counseling deemed appropriate by agent.  

AODA and follow up.  

DNA sample.  

COURT has no objection to transferring probation to Clark County.

result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Dustin D. Dietsche

records.addlTxt:
Clerk: Amy. 
Case called:  3:02 p.m. 

State appears by ADA Natalie Zibolski.  Defendant appears in person with Atty Dave Casey.  

Date and time set for initial appearance.preliminary hearing/plea hearing; VRCW.  

INITIAL APPEARANCE/WAIVER OF PRELIMINARY HEARING>>
COURT questions deft as to waiver.
COURT finds waiver freely and voluntarily made.
COURT finds PC - Defendant bound over for arraignment & trial. 
Information will be e-filed.

COURT ORDERS: $2500.00 signature bond.

CONDITIONS: 
- No contact with victim(s): B.L.L. unless approved by agent. 


PLEA/SENTENCING>>>
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights filed.  
COURT advises defendant of rights (including constitutional rights) & penalties & questions defendant to understanding.
COURT finds plea & waiver of rights freely & voluntary made, a factual basis & defendant guilty.

PLEA: 
Count 1 (Expose Child to Harmful Descriptions): GUILTY.  
Count 2 (Sexual Intercourse with Child Age 15 or Older): GUILTY.  
Count 3 (Exposing Genitals): GUILTY.  
Count 4 (Disorderly Conduct): GUILTY. 

COURT w/holds finding and entry of guilt on COUNT 1.  COURT adopts written deferred entry of judgment agreement as signed by all parties and submitted to COURT.
COURT defers Count 1 for a period of 3.5 years for defendant to comply with all terms and conditions of written DEJ agreement.
If defendant is in full compliance with all terms and conditions of written DEOJ agreement within that time frame and obtains no new criminal charges, State to DISMISS Count 1. 

COURT ORDERS on Count 2, 3 and 4: SWH for 2 years probation; concurrent with each other.  CONDITIONS:  Sex Offender assessment, treatment, counseling.  Any other Assessments/Treatment/Counseling deemed appropriate by agent.  Maintain FTW/School or combination of the two, and if not so fully engaged, complete 10 hours CS per week.  Maintain absolute sobriety from and no possession of alcohol.  No bars, taverns, liquors stores and beer tents.  AODA and follow up.  No contact with victim, B.L.L. unless approved by agent.  No contact with females under the age of 18, or as approved by agent, excluding incidentals while at work.  No use of any social media including SnapChat. Court costs including DNA sample/surcharge.  

COURT has no objection to transferring probation to Clark County.  

DEOJ review hearing>>>10/21/2025 at 9:00 a.m. 

Bond continues.  

Adj:  3:27 p.m.
